Summay of circle experiment.

Jesse Leigh Patsolic

Problem statment

Consider a 100-gon where 10 vertices are colored 1 and the rest are colored 0 according to the following rules:

  • Class 1 consists of two groups of 5 contiguous vertices colored 1.
  • Class 2 consists of two groups of 6 and 4 contiguous vertices, respectively, colored 1.

sampling

set.seed(317)
c1 <- 100
c2 <- 100

X1 <- foreach(i = 1:c1, .combine = rbind) %do% {
  set.seed(i)
  cir <- rep(0,100)

  s1 <- sample(0:99, 1)
  l1 <- s1:(s1 + 4) %% 100

  s2 <- sample(setdiff(0:99, unique(c(l1, l1 - 4))), 1)
  l2 <- s2:(s2 + 4) %% 100

  cir[l1 + 1] <- 1
  cir[l2 + 1] <- 1

  cir
}

X2 <- foreach(i = 1:c2, .combine = rbind) %do% {
  set.seed(i)
  cir <- rep(0,100)

  s1 <- sample(0:99, 1)
  l1 <- s1:(s1 + 5) %% 100

  s2 <- sample(setdiff(0:99, unique(c(l1, l1 - 3))), 1)
  l2 <- s2:(s2 + 3) %% 100

  cir[l1 + 1] <- 1
  cir[l2 + 1] <- 1

  cir
}

As an image

X <- rbind(X1, X2)
v <- as.raster(rbind(X1, X2))
plot(v)

As Circles

cs <- seq(0, 2 * pi - (2 * pi / 100), length = 100)

x <- lapply(cs, sin)
y <- lapply(cs, cos)

set.seed(317)
par(mfrow = c(5,5))
for(j in sort(sample(nrow(X), 25))) {
  par(mar = c(1,1,1,1))
  plot(x, y, col = c('gray90', 'red')[X[j, ] + 1], asp = 1,
       pch = 19, xaxt='n', yaxt='n', xlab = '', ylab = '',
       cex = 0.5)
  text(0,0, label = j)
}
